The paper deals with compressive sensing (CS) and sparse recovery, which are core topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus is on one-bit CS, which is a specific area of CS that has received significant attention in recent years. The paper also discusses adaptive sampling, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper uses tools from high-dimensional geometry, which is a topic in mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.MM).
